{
  "info": {
    "name": "gRPC Inventory System",
    "_postman_id": "grpc-inventory-collection-v2",
    "description": "# gRPC Inventory System API\n\nThis collection covers the **REST Inventory API** (port `8080`) that sits in front of the **gRPC server** (port `50051`).\n\n## Architecture\n```\nPostman / gRPC Client\n       │\n       ▼\n REST API  (:8080)   ←── this collection tests these endpoints\n       │\n       ▼\n gRPC Server (:50051)  ←── gRPC requests use Postman's native gRPC tab\n```\n\n## Environments\nUse the bundled **Local** environment for `localhost` testing or the **Docker** environment for containerised runs.\n\n## Authentication\nNo auth required in this build. Add a Bearer token variable (`{{api_token}}`) when you enable JWT middleware.\n\n## Low-stock threshold\nItems with `quantity < 50` are considered low stock.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": {
      "major": 2,
      "minor": 0,
      "patch": 0
    }
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "grpc_host",
      "value": "localhost:50051",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "created_sku",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "description": "Quick sanity-check requests to confirm the service is reachable.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Ping – REST API",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('REST API is reachable (2xx or 404)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Response time < 500 ms', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(500);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/healthz",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "healthz"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Fetches a known SKU. A 200 confirms both the server and data store are healthy."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST API – Read",
      "description": "GET endpoints: fetch a single SKU and list low-stock items.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Stock – MED-001 (Amoxicillin)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is JSON', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/json');",
                  "});",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('SKU matches', () => pm.expect(body.sku).to.eql('MED-001'));",
                  "pm.test('medicine_name is present', () => pm.expect(body.medicine_name).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.test('quantity is a non-negative integer', () => pm.expect(body.quantity).to.be.a('number').and.at.least(0));",
                  "pm.test('requires_prescription is boolean', () => pm.expect(body.requires_prescription).to.be.a('boolean'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/inventory/MED-001",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "inventory",
                "MED-001"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Fetches the stock record for `MED-001` (Amoxicillin 500mg)."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 – Found",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/inventory/MED-001"
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [
                {
                  "key": "Content-Type",
                  "value": "application/json"
                }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"sku\": \"MED-001\",\n  \"medicine_name\": \"Amoxicillin 500mg\",\n  \"quantity\": 1450,\n  \"requires_prescription\": true\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
